HEADWORD: Catadrome
<hw>Cat"a*drome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kata`dromos</grk> race course; <grk>kata`</grk> down +
<grk>dro`mos</grk> course.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A race
course.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A machine for raising or lowering
heavy weights.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catadromous</ent>⟦br⟧
